libliftoff
------------------------------------------
libliftoff eases the use of KMS planes from userspace without standing in your
way. Users create virtual planes called layers, set KMS properties on them, and
libliftoff will pick planes for these layers if possible.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.4.6-1
  libdrm-devel-2.4.115-1bl1
  libdrm2-2.4.115-1bl1
  libliftoff-devel-0.4.1-1bl1
  libliftoff0-0.4.1-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.9.4-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.40-1
  cygport-0.36.1-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  libdrm-devel-2.4.115-1bl1
  meson-0.63.3-1
  ninja-1.11.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/emersion/libliftoff

Canonical download:
  https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/emersion/libliftoff/-/archive/v0.4.1/libliftoff-v0.4.1.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libliftoff-0.4.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libliftoff-0.4.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libliftoff-0.4.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libliftoff-0.4.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libliftoff0-0.4.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libliftoff-devel-0.4.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libliftoff)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libliftoff.README
  /usr/share/doc/libliftoff/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/libliftoff/README.md

(libliftoff0)
  /usr/bin/cygliftoff-0.dll

(libliftoff-devel)
  /usr/include/libliftoff.h
  /usr/lib/libliftoff.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libliftoff.pc

